comments.message:
@Jeremy sure as you have suggested the discovery and management of endpoints shall be handled by a dedicated process but that process should abstractly handle both MCTP and RBT endpoints.

@Tom I agree and i will add more detail on how PLDM requests are further transitioned at MCTP and RBT layer.
but the basic idea is we first  discover MCTP and RBT endpoints and create a one to one map of these endpoints MCTP example : (TID<->EID<->SOCKET) .
when sending the PLDM requests to the endpoints, a common PLDM transport wrapper api is called which accepts only the TID of a pldm endpoint  and the PLDM request as parameters.Then internally the PLDM transport wrapper api checks the one-to-one TID map which we have created to get the corresponding socket connection(MCTP socket or NCSI socket) to send the request as respective transport layer request(MCTP or RBT).
